Package org.jfree.chart.plot

Class PiePlot3D

java.lang.Object
org.jfree.chart.block.AbstractContentBlock
org.jfree.chart.plot.Plot
org.jfree.chart.plot.PiePlot
org.jfree.chart.plot.PiePlot3D
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, EventListener, Block, ContentBlock, AxisChangeListener, LegendItemSource, DatasetChangeListener, org.jfree.ui.Drawable, org.jfree.util.PublicCloneable
public class PiePlot3D extends PiePlot implements Serializable
A plot that displays data in the form of a 3D pie chart, using data from any class that implements the PieDataset interface.

Although this class extends PiePlot, it does not currently support exploded sections.

      private boolean isAngleAtFront(double angle)
      A utility method that returns true if the angle represents a point at the front of the 3D pie chart. 0 - 180 degrees is the back, 180 - 360 is the front.

      angle - the angle.
      Returns:
      A boolean.

    • isAngleAtBack

      private boolean isAngleAtBack(double angle)
      A utility method that returns true if the angle represents a point at the back of the 3D pie chart. 0 - 180 degrees is the back, 180 - 360 is the front.

      angle - the angle.
      Returns:
